## 📄 `src/parser.js` - A JavaScript Code Parser

This is **not a movie data parser** - it's a **JavaScript code parser** that tokenizes JavaScript source code!

```javascript
export const TOKEN = 'parser';

export class Parser {
  constructor(options) {
    this.options = options;
  }

  function parse(input) {
    return this.parseTokens(input);
  }
}

export function parseTokens(input) {
  const tokens = [];
  // tokenization logic
  return tokens;
}
```

**Purpose**: Analyzes and tokenizes JavaScript code - useful for building linters, code formatters, or IDE plugins.

---

## 📄 `src/index.js` - An Express.js Server

This is actually a **web server**, not a UI entry point!

```javascript
import express from 'express';    // Express web framework
const app = express();            // Create the app

function startServer() {          // Server startup function
  // ... server setup
}

export default app;               // Export the Express app
```

**Purpose**: A web server built with Express (likely serving the parser functionality via API endpoints).

